tooltip.groove_depth=Radial depth; X is diameter (G7). X change = 2 * depth.
tooltip.groove_diameter=Target diameter of the groove or plunge cut.
tooltip.groove_finish=Finish allowance is radial; X is diameter (G7).
tooltip.groove_tool=Tool used for grooving or parting.
tooltip.groove_spindle=Spindle speed or cutting speed for this groove/parting step.
tooltip.groove_coolant=Turn coolant on during grooving or parting.
tooltip.groove_process_type=Groove shows only groove parameters, Parting reveals extra parting parameters.
tooltip.groove_width=Overall groove width in Z.
tooltip.groove_cutting_width=Effective insert width; important for multi-pass grooving.
tooltip.groove_z=Z position or reference position of the groove.
tooltip.groove_feed=Working feed for grooving or parting.
tooltip.groove_safe_z=Safe Z position before approaching the groove.
tooltip.groove_lage=Choose OD, ID, or face-side groove orientation.
tooltip.groove_ref=Choose whether Z refers to the center, left flank, or right flank.
tooltip.groove_overlap=Side overlap between neighboring groove passes.
tooltip.groove_reduced_feed=Reduced feed for the final parting zone.
tooltip.groove_reduced_feed_start_x=Switch to reduced parting feed from this X diameter onward.
tooltip.groove_reduced_rpm=Reduced spindle speed for the final parting zone.
tooltip.groove_retract=Retract is radial; X is diameter (G7).
tooltip.groove_sweep_feed=Additional feed used for chip-breaking or sweeping moves inside the groove.
tooltip.groove_chip_amp=Amplitude of the chip-breaking motion inside the groove.
tooltip.groove_chip_n=Number of chip-breaking cycles per groove step.
tooltip.groove_step_a=Depth per pass is radial; X is diameter (G7).
tooltip.groove_use_tool_width=If enabled, cutter width is managed separately from the groove width.
tooltip.parting_contour=Contour referenced by this roughing step.
tooltip.parting_side=Choose OD or ID machining; this affects safety logic and generated motion.
tooltip.parting_tool=Tool used for this roughing step.
tooltip.parting_spindle=Spindle speed or cutting speed for this roughing step.
tooltip.parting_coolant=Turn coolant on for this roughing step.
tooltip.parting_feed=Working feed for roughing/finishing this contour.
tooltip.parting_depth_per_pass=Maximum depth of cut per roughing pass.
tooltip.parting_mode=Rough only, finish only, or both in this step.
tooltip.parting_pause_enabled=Enable short feed pauses for chip breaking.
tooltip.parting_pause_distance=Travel distance between two feed pauses.
tooltip.parting_allow_undercut=Allow undercuts (cut beyond contour)
tooltip.parting_finish_allow_x=Radial finish allowance during roughing
tooltip.parting_finish_allow_z=Axial finish allowance during roughing
tooltip.parting_optional_stop_before_undercut=Insert an optional M1 stop before the separate relief/undercut pass.
tooltip.parting_output_preference=Prefer canned cycle output or explicit toolpath output when both are possible.
tooltip.parting_slice_step=Step between X-bands (mm)
tooltip.parting_slice_strategy=Choose the roughing direction (axis-aligned: Parallel X or Parallel Z).
tooltip.parting_undercut_feed=Dedicated feed for the separate relief/undercut pass.
tooltip.parting_undercut_mode=Choose whether reliefs are ignored, finished only, roughed separately, or fully included in the contour.
tooltip.parting_undercut_spindle=Dedicated spindle speed for the separate relief/undercut pass.
tooltip.parting_undercut_tool=Separate tool for relief/undercut when 'Rough separately' is selected.
tooltip.program_chuck_x_max=Maximum allowed X diameter outside the chuck no-go area.
tooltip.program_chuck_x_min=Minimum allowed X diameter outside the chuck no-go area.
tooltip.program_chuck_z_limit=Z limit of the chuck no-go area. Moves crossing it are warned.
tooltip.program_l=Length L for stock shapes that require an additional length value.
tooltip.program_language=Select the panel language for labels and tooltips.
tooltip.program_n=Number of edges N for polygonal stock shapes.
tooltip.program_npv=Work offset / work coordinate system used by the program, for example G54 to G59.3.
tooltip.program_optional_stop_toolchange=Insert an optional M1 stop before every tool change.
tooltip.program_park_coords=Choose whether park X/Z are emitted as work coordinates or machine coordinates using G53.
tooltip.program_park_mode=Choose whether the program ends at the tool change point or a custom park position.
tooltip.program_park_sequential=Move X and Z sequentially instead of diagonally for a tighter final park move.
tooltip.program_park_x=X position for a custom park move at program end.
tooltip.program_park_z=Z position for a custom park move at program end.
tooltip.program_preview_warnings=Show safety and plausibility warnings directly in the preview.
tooltip.program_retract_mode=Choose which retract planes are available and relevant for generator and preview: simple, extended, or all.
tooltip.program_shape=Base stock shape. This affects visible input fields and parts of the preview.
tooltip.program_spindle_max_rpm=Maximum RPM for CSS/G96 to avoid overspeed on small diameters.
tooltip.program_spindle_mode=Select fixed RPM G97 or constant surface speed G96.
tooltip.program_sw=Across-flats size SW for matching polygonal stock shapes.
tooltip.program_toolchange_coords=Choose whether XT/ZT are emitted as work coordinates or machine coordinates using G53.
tooltip.program_unit=Choose whether program data is entered and emitted in millimeters or inches.
tooltip.program_w=Width W for non-cylindrical stock shapes such as rectangle or polygon.
tooltip.program_xa=Outer stock diameter at the start. Enter as a diameter value in G7 mode.
tooltip.program_xi=Inner stock diameter when using tube stock or internal machining.
tooltip.program_xra=Outer X retract plane for safe moves outside the part.
tooltip.program_xri=Inner X retract plane for internal machining and bores.
tooltip.program_za=Front start dimension in Z. This defines the axial stock start position.
tooltip.program_zb=Machining Z limit. Used as a reference for chuck and safety logic.
tooltip.program_zi=Rear end dimension in Z. Together with ZA this defines the stock length.
tooltip.program_zra=Outer Z retract plane for safe approach and retract moves.
tooltip.program_zri=Inner Z retract plane for retracts during internal machining.
tooltip.thread_depth=Adjust if needed (material gives way)
tooltip.thread_standard=Thread preset with nominal diameter, pitch, and suggested values.
tooltip.thread_orientation=Choose external or internal threading; this changes safety and generator behavior.
tooltip.thread_hand=Choose right-hand or left-hand thread; this controls Z direction and spindle behavior.
tooltip.thread_e=G76-E (finish/option)
tooltip.thread_first_depth=First cut; remainder distributed
tooltip.thread_infeed_q=Infeed angle Q (°)
tooltip.thread_l=G76-L (option / multi-start)
tooltip.thread_length=Z end relative/absolute – depends on model
tooltip.thread_tool=Tool used for this threading step.
tooltip.thread_spindle=Spindle speed or cutting speed for threading.
tooltip.thread_coolant=Turn coolant on during threading.
tooltip.thread_major_diameter=Nominal or major diameter of the thread.
tooltip.thread_passes=Rough passes (count)
tooltip.thread_peak_offset=For crest/face offset; often negative
tooltip.thread_pitch=Thread pitch per revolution.
tooltip.thread_retract_r=Retract at end of cut
tooltip.thread_relief_mode=Control whether a DIN relief is suggested or ignored.
tooltip.thread_relief_norm=Choose the DIN variant used for the suggested thread relief.
tooltip.thread_safe_z=Start point before G76/G32
tooltip.thread_spring_passes=Spring passes (count)
tooltip.thread_start_z=Z start position of the thread. Right-hand threads usually run toward negative Z, left-hand threads toward positive Z.
tooltip.thread_optional_stop_before=Insert an optional M1 stop before this threading step.
tooltip.btn_thread_preset=Apply the selected preset to all thread parameters of this step.
